{"name": "string-color", "metadata": {"name": "string-color", "version": "1.2.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://gitlab.com/shindagger/string-color", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["setuptools", "columnar", "colorama"], "summary": "just another mod to print strings in 256 colors in the terminal.", "upload_time": 1652215450}, "documentation": ["# string-color   \n\nstring-color is just another python module for coloring strings in print statements.   \n\n### Installation   \n\n`$ pip install string-color`   \n\n### Python Module Usage   \n\n```python   \nfrom stringcolor import * \n\n# a few examples without background colors.   \n# for color names see CLI usage below.   \nprint(cs(\"here we go\", \"orchid\"))   \nprint(cs(\"away to space!\", \"DeepPink3\"))   \nprint(cs(\"final fantasy\", \"#ffff87\"))   \nprint()  \n\n# bold and underline also available.  \nprint(cs(\"purple number 4, bold\", \"purple4\").bold())  \nprint(cs(\"blue, underlined\", \"blue\").underline())  \nprint(bold(\"bold AND underlined!\").underline().cs(\"red\", \"gold\"))\nprint(underline(\"the bottom line.\"))\nprint()\n\n# yellow text with a red background.   \n# color names, hex values, and ansi numbers will work.   \nprint(cs(\"warning!\", \"yellow\", \"#ff0000\")) \nprint()\n\n# concat\nprint(cs(\"wild\", \"pink\")+\" stuff\")\nprint(\"nothing \"+cs(\"something\", \"DarkViolet2\", \"lightgrey6\"))\nprint()\n\n# use any working rgb or hex values.\n# it will find the closest color available.\nprint(cs(\"this will show up red\", \"#ff0009\"))\nprint(cs(\"so will this\", \"rgb(254, 0, 1)\"))\nprint()\n\n# use with format and f-strings\nprint(f\"this is a test {cs('to check formatting with f-strings', 'yellow', 'grey').bold().underline()}\")\nprint(\"this is a test {}\".format(cs('to check the format function', 'purple', 'lightgrey11').bold().underline()))\n```   \n\n![Usage Screep Cap][screencap]\n\n[screencap]: https://believe-it-or-not-im-walking-on-air.s3.amazonaws.com/sc-screen-cap.jpg \"Usage Screen Cap\"\n\n### CLI Usage     \n\n```\nusage: string-color [-h] [-x] [-r] [-t] [--hsl] [-a] [-i] [-v] [color]\n\njust another mod for printing strings in color.\n\npositional arguments:\n  color          show info for a specific color:\n                 $ string-color red\n                 $ string-color '#ffff87'\n                 $ string-color *grey* # wildcards acceptable\n                 $ string-color '#E16A7F' # any hex not found will return the closest match\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help     show this help message and exit\n  -x, --hex      show hex values\n  -r, --rgb      show rgb values\n  -t, --term     show term numbers\n  --hsl          show hsl values\n  -a, --alpha    sort by name\n  -i, --inverse  show inverse colors\n  -v, --version  show program's version number and exit\n```  \n\n`$ string-color`   \n\ndisplay a list of all 256 colors   \n\n`$ string-color yellow`   \n\nshow color info for the color yellow   \n\n`$ string-color \"#ff0000\"`   \n\nshow color info for the hex value #ff0000   \n\n`$ string-color *grey*`  \n\nshow all colors with \"grey\" in the name. also works with \"grey\\*\" and \"\\*grey\"  \n\n![CLI Screep Cap][cliscreencap]  \n\n[cliscreencap]: https://believe-it-or-not-im-walking-on-air.s3.amazonaws.com/sc-screen-cap2.jpg  \"CLI Screen Cap\"  \n\n\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "stringcolor.test", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "stringcolor", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "stringcolor.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "stringcolor.bold", "xref": {"fqname": "stringcolor.ops.Bold", "project": null}}, {"name": "stringcolor.cs", "xref": {"fqname": "stringcolor.ops.Color", "project": null}}, {"name": "stringcolor.underline", "xref": {"fqname": "stringcolor.ops.Underline", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "stringcolor.main", "documentation": ["just another mod for printing strings in color.", "!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [{"name": "stringcolor.main.sort_by_alpha", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["sort dictionary by name alphabetically"]}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.signal_handler", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "frame", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["handle control c"]}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.find_colors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "color", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["find colors matching args"]}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["just another mod for printing strings in color.\n\nCLI entry point."]}], "variables": [{"name": "stringcolor.main.COLORS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.cs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.rgbtolist", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.hextorgb", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.main.color_difference", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.quote_page", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.page", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.soup", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.cd", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.term", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "stringcolor.delete-later.chex", "type": 